BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:_vxPsNi-JLQLqxzfMDWA5
SUMMARY:Physical Humor 100: The Comic Technician with Mick Holsbeke
DTSTAMP:20260306T004520Z
DTSTART:20260305T173000Z
DESCRIPTION:Get silly\\\, take bold creative risks\\\, and find the funny t
	hrough ensemble improv\\\, physical comedy\\\, and playful clown-inspired 
	games.\\n\\n\\n\\nEver since we were able to stand\\\, we have been able t
	o fall\\\, and humans love to laugh at someone who stumbles\\\, trips\\\, 
	bobbles\\\, bumps into\\\, gets hit by\\\, or struggles with problems that
	 should be easily avoidable or\\\, otherwise\\\, are simple to solve. In t
	his class series\\\, internationally renowned clown & circus artist Mick H
	olsbeke will guide students through an introduction to the foundations of 
	Physical Comedy\\\, offering participants a broad range of experience in t
	he joys of being clumsy\\\, accident-prone comic characters. \\nClass Deta
	ils\\nDates: 3/5/26 thru 4/9/26\; Six (6) Thursday classes \\nTime: 5:30 P
	M – 7:00 PM \\nLocation: The Clown Garage at the Improv School Eastside Is
	saquah \\n1315 NW Mall Street\\\, Suite 4 Issaquah\\\, WA 98027 (next to t
	he Gaslamp Bar & Grill) \\nMaximum students: 12 \\nAges: 18 plus \\nCost: 
	$320 \\nPrerequisite: Clown 100\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/e
	vent/physical-humor-100-the-comic-technician-with-mick-holsbeke/\n\nFrom U
	nexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/physical-humor-100-the-comi
	c-technician-with-mick-holsbeke/
LOCATION:Clown Garage at the Improv School Issaquah\\\, 1315 NW Mall Street
	\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98027
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:GhKrzqepCnigEjTk-anZt
SUMMARY:Clown 100: The Foundations of Clown Play with Mick Holsbeke
DTSTAMP:20260306T004520Z
DTSTART:20260305T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Step into the playful world of Clown! Explore presence\\\, vuln
	erability\\\, and joyful failure through ensemble play and laughter\\n\\n\
	\n\\nWelcome to the world of clowning! This foundational class invites you
	 to step into the playful\\\, unpredictable\\\, and joy-filled realm of Cl
	owning with other folks. Through a series of dynamic exercises in presence
	\\\, play\\\, rhythm\\\, tension\\\, emotional expression\\\, and ensemble
	 play\\\, participants will explore what makes Clown so hilarious and cont
	agious. Embracing vulnerability and the fine art of making mistakes\\\, we
	’ll turn failure into laughter and endless comic gold. Whether you’re new 
	to performance or a seasoned artist\\\, this series will help you build co
	nfidence\\\, take creative risks\\\, and refine your Clown instincts. Come
	 ready to play\\\, surprise yourself\\\, and find the fun in the unexpecte
	d! \\nClass Details\\nDates: 3/5/26 thru 4/9/26\; Six (6) Thursday classes
	 \\nTime: 7:00 pm to 8:30 pm \\nLocation: The Clown Garage at Improv Schoo
	l Eastside Issaquah \\n1315 NW Mall Street\\\, Suite 4 Issaquah\\\, WA 980
	27 (next to the Gaslamp Bar & Grill) \\nMaximum students: 16 \\nAges: 18 p
	lus \\nCost: $320 \\nPrerequisite: None\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductio
	ns.org/event/clown-100-the-foundations-of-clown-play-with-mick-holsbeke-2/
	\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/clown-100-the-foundations-o
	f-clown-play-with-mick-holsbeke-2/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\\\, 1428 Post Alley at the Gum Wall in Pike
	 Place Market\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:IoWop0mgsTasw0e8sUKeG
SUMMARY:Loose Cannons 2026
DTSTAMP:20260306T004520Z
DTSTART:20260305T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Loose Cannons is Seattle improv at its most unpredictable. Ever
	y performance at Unexpected Productions in Pike Place Market is a one-of-a
	-kind experience: exciting\\\, unexpected\\\, a little dangerous\\\, and a
	lways ridiculously fun. This is the show where anything can happen and usu
	ally does. \\nPart One: Part One: The night kicks off with a unique perfor
	mance\\\, setting the performers in a new format with special guest improv
	isers showcasing their signature style or a never-before-seen format. Your
	 suggestions fuel the fire\\\, and the improvisers will ignite the stage\\
	\, bringing your ideas to life. \\nPart Two: The second half launches from
	 a single audience suggestion\\\, setting the performers in motion. It mig
	ht start with a song\\\, a monologue\\\, or a rapid-fire group connection 
	game. Whatever emerges will inspire spontaneous stories\\\, surprising twi
	sts\\\, and big comedic swings. \\nLoose Cannons is fueled by audience ide
	as\\\, fearless performers\\\, and the thrill of not knowing what happens 
	next. You light the fuse. They run with it. What they create is entirely u
	p to you.\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/loose-cannons-202
	6/2026-03-05/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/loose-cannons-2026/2026-03-
	05/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\\\, 1428 Post Alley at the Gum Wall in Pike
	 Place Market\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98101\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
